For, needy, unknown, and restless, he wound himself by secret information into the favour of the cruel emperor, and subsequently en— dangered all the citizens of renown3 and having gained influence with one man, and the hatred of everybody else, he set a precedent followed by men, who thus becoming rich instead of poor, objects of fear instead of objects of contempt, brought ruin upon' others, and *finally upon themselves.
